      "writtenOn": "2018-06-04T15:51:33Z",
      "side": 1,
      "message": "i didn\u0027t realize that you plan to use all repos in blamelist computation. This is interesting and I agree we should support it.\n\nthis is not obvious for most of blamelist users though. The default should be only the repo specified in the builder (e.g. a chromium builder sends blamelist emails only to authors of chromium CLs, and not V8 commits). Can we add \"Repository\" into the BlamelistNotification message? If not specified, it defaults to Builder.reposotory. If \"*\" or something like that, then all repos, i.e what you do here",
      "revId": "0ae4858bf1590fda9d98044e39261ac37cc57232",
      "serverId": "3ce6091f-6c88-37e8-8c75-72f92ae8dfba",
      "unresolved": true
    },
