      "writtenOn": "2018-06-05T21:06:51Z",
      "side": 1,
      "message": "actually, I\u0027m not sure how this would work...\n\nthe whole reason Builder.repository is there is to pick a repository we\u0027re checking commits against for ordering. if we use \"*\" to indicate multiple repos, we can no longer use a repo for ordering and only build time. I think it\u0027s desirable to be able to determine ordering based on a certain repo, but also use all the repos that went into the change as a blamelist. in fact, this exactly covers our use-case right now.",
      "parentUuid": "9375ca65_106ba315",
